Lewis Hamilton  of McLaren won the
Canadian Grand Prix for his first victory of the Formula One
season.  Romain Grosjean of Lotus was second, followed by Sergio
Perez of Sauber at the 2.14-mile (4.36 kilometer), Circuit
Gilles Villeneuve around the streets of Montreal.  Hamiltonâ€™s victory means a different driver has won each of
the seven opening races of the season for the first time in the
